-------------------------------------------------------------------

BioSync Backend Environment Configuration (.env.example)

This file lists all required environment variables.

-------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Django Core Settings

SECRET_KEY=your_very_secure_django_secret_key_here
DEBUG=True
ALLOWED_HOSTS=127.0.0.1,localhost

2. Database (PostgreSQL)

DB_ENGINE=django.db.backends.postgresql
DB_NAME=biosync_db
DB_USER=biosync_user
DB_PASSWORD=strong_db_password
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432

3. Security & CORS

Set to 'http://localhost:3000' for the Next.js web frontend

Set to 'http://localhost:19006' for the Expo/React Native mobile app (running on web)

CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:19006

4. External API Integration

WGER API is used for exercise metadata (names, descriptions, muscles)

WGER_API_BASE_URL=https://wger.de/api/v2/
WGER_API_KEY=your_optional_wger_api_key

5. Media Storage (For User Profile Pictures)

If using a cloud provider (e.g., S3), set credentials here.

For local development, these can be empty, but we include them for completeness.

AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_STORAGE_BUCKET_NAME=
